Classes in org.ndnx.ndn used by org.ndnx.ndn
ContentVerifier
          A callback interface to allow low-level mechanisms to ask someone else to verify content on their behalf.
KeyManager
          Top-level interface for managing our own keys, as well as maintaining an address book containing the keys of others (which will be used by the TrustManager).
NDNBase
          This is the lowest-level interface to NDN, and describes in its entirety, the interface the library has to speak to the NDN network layer.
NDNContentHandler
          A handler used to receive callbacks when data arrives matching one of our asynchronously-expressed Interests (expressed with NDNBase#expressInterest(Interest, NDNInterestHandler)).
NDNFilterListener
          Deprecated. 
NDNHandle
          The core class encapsulating a Java interface to the NDN network.
NDNInterestHandler
          A NDN filter is essentially an "interest in Interests" -- it allows a caller to register to see Interest messages that come in from the network, and optionally generate (or merely provide) data in response.
NDNInterestListener
          Deprecated. 
NDNSyncHandler
           
TrustManager
          Basic interface to trust management -- determination of whether a piece of content is acceptable to a given consumer for a particular use in a particular content.
